# ============================================================================
# TireShopPOS: Crontab Configuration
# ============================================================================
#
# Install with: crontab deploy/crontab.example
# Or edit:      crontab -e
#
# Replace /home/user/domains/pos.example.com/app with your actual app path.
# All output goes to storage/logs/cron.log via the cron-runner.
#
# DunganSoft Technologies, March 2026
# ============================================================================

# ---- PATHS ----
# Adjust this to your installation directory.
APP=/home/user/domains/pos.example.com/app

# ============================================================================
# Option A: Simple (2 crontab lines)
# ============================================================================
# The cron-runner orchestrates all jobs with file locking.
# "all-frequent" runs every 5 min: notifications, webhooks, sessions (15 min).
# "all-daily" runs at 2 AM: backups, log rotation, rate limit cleanup.

*/5 * * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh all-frequent  >> /dev/null 2>&1
0   2 * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh all-daily     >> /dev/null 2>&1

# ============================================================================
# Option B: Granular (individual control)
# ============================================================================
# Uncomment these instead of Option A for per-job scheduling.

# Session cleanup: every 15 minutes
# */15 * * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh sessions        >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Notification delivery: every 5 minutes
# */5  * * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh notifications   >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Webhook retry: every 5 minutes
# */5  * * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh webhooks        >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Rate limit cleanup: every hour
# 0    * * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh rate-limits     >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Database backup: daily at 2 AM
# 0    2 * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh backup-db       >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Photo backup: daily at 2:30 AM
# 30   2 * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh backup-photos   >> /dev/null 2>&1

# Log rotation: daily at midnight
# 0    0 * * *  $APP/scripts/cron-runner.sh rotate-logs     >> /dev/null 2>&1

# ============================================================================
# Monitoring
# ============================================================================
# Check cron status:
#   ./scripts/cron-runner.sh status
#
# View cron log:
#   tail -50 storage/logs/cron.log
#
# Test a specific job:
#   ./scripts/cron-runner.sh notifications
#
# Verify crontab installed:
#   crontab -l
